- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with community structure in networks and graph generation.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses a methodology for generating synthetic graphs.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a low-rank approximation of the modularity matrix to generate synthetic graphs.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses techniques for generating random graphs.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses a method for generating synthetic graphs that can be extended to target other properties beyond modularity.
